<item>
            <title>[LU-15991] kernel update [RHEL7.9 3.10.0-1160.71.1.el7]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15991</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: race condition in perf_event_open leads to privilege escalation (CVE-2022-1729)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: a use-after-free write in the netfilter subsystem can lead to privilege escalation to root (CVE-2022-1966)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Bug Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;XFS inode cluster corruption (BZ#2050464)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;sock: sock_dequeue_err_skb() needs hard irq safety (BZ#2070408)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;libceph: fix potential use-after-free on linger ping and resends (BZ#2088025)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:5232&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2022:5232&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
